work in progress code snippets for coming soon median finding experiment
see http://matpalm.com/median

-----------------
generate a list of (approx) 1000 numbers whose min is 1, max is 100 and median is 40
spread this across 4 files; numbers.0, numbers.1, numbers.2, numbers.3

bash> ./generate_test_data.rb 1 40 100 1000 > numbers.all
bash> cat numbers.all | ./spread_across_files.rb numbers 4

-----------------
run ruby version

bash> cat numbers.all | ./median.rb

-----------------
run erlang single process version

bash> erl -noshell -s median from_file numbers.all -s init stop 

-----------------
run erlang multiple process version (all processes on local machine) using full list impl

bash> erl -noshell -s controller init worker numbers.[0-3] -s init stop

-----------------
run erlang multiple process version (all processes on local machine) usnig list freq impl

bash> erl -noshell -s controller init worker_freq numbers.[0-3] -s init stop

